==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Catenulate
<hw>Ca*ten"u*late</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>catenuia</ets>, dim. of <ets>catena</ets> chain.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Consisting of little links or chains.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Chainlike; -- said both or color
marks and of indentations when arranged like the links of a chain, as on
shells, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cater</ent>⟦br⟧
